        public void addNewCustomer(String row,
                           Type type,
                           int id)
        If a contact (with just an email or phone number as well) is not matched by any other customer, then a new customer is created.
        Parameters:
        row - is the contact row i.e. email or phone number
        type - is the type of contact row so as to know whether the row is email or number
        id - is the insertation number given by the source system or the file that is downloaded to the system

      • createAndUpdate

        public void createAndUpdate(Integer key,
                            ContactList list)

        list - is the ContactList that we are comparing to these customers

        Customers can be created and found by customer number or insertation number.
        Parameters:
        key - is the key of ContactList, each key can have one to many rows of contact data
        i - is the number of row in StateKeeper tables
        eye - is the StateKeeper panel that keeps track of each contact row and their status

      • stateNotFound

                          StateKeeper sk,
                          int k,
                          int key,
                          ContactList list)
        Contact rows are added to StateKeeper object if they are not found in the customer list.
        Parameters:
        row - is the contact row i.e. email or phone number
        sk - is the StateKeeper where contact rows are added
        k - is table number in StateKeeper object
        key - is the key number in the Map of contactList
        list - is the ContactList itself

      • find

        public Customer find(Integer key,
                     ContactList list)
        A customer can be found from the ContactList if at least one hashCode is same with customers hashCodes.
        Parameters:
        key - is the key that indicates one or several rows of inserted contact info.
        list - is the ContactList we want to compare with the existing customers.
        Returns:
        a customer if ContactList have a same contact info according to hashCode search.
